    "His article on the subject was sent to the <em>Architectural Review</em>.": [],
    "At the encouragement of its editor, <a href=\"/pevsnern\">Nikolaus Bernard Leon Pevsner</a>, Fleming wrote more, including articles on Maltese churches and baroque sculpture and contemporary Italian painting (the latter for <em>Penguin New Writing</em>).": [],
    "The war years brought him in contact with art historian <a href=\"/waterhousee\">Ellis K. Waterhouse</a>, then a colonel, though they did not get along, and expatriate German art historians such as <a href=\"/wittkowerr\">Rudolf Wittkower</a>.": [],
    "After the war, Fleming appeased his father by working as a solicitor with the John Hilton Advice bureau at Cambridge.": [],
